Pistol had a handful of failure to ejects in the 2-300 rounds I've put through it. Steps have been taken to attempt to fix it, but haven't had time to test them (hence the numbered magazines).

title: For Sale:  5.56 Green Tip ammo (XM855) LC/FC in Bandoleers/strippers
location: Northeast Suburban St. Paul, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
Packed in proper cans and bandoleers, I am selling this by the Bandoleer....$60 cash for one bandoleer of 120 rounds.

This is the green tip steel core "Penetrator" stuff that the Feds tried to ban but backed off. It is available commercially in boxes at stores and gun shows or bulk from a couple wholesalers and this is packed carefully in surplus USGI bandoleers, stripper clips and the cans too, and is pretty close to how it comes packaged for our troops.
120 rounds to a bandoleer, seven bandoleers packed in a .50 caliber can (840 rounds total) that is properly marked for these bandoleers of this ammo. 

Each bandoleer has four pockets.
Each pocket contains a cardboard sleeve that holds three stripper clips, with 10 rounds each so you can fill a 30 round magazine from each pocket. There is also a "loading spoon" in one end pocket to load M4/M16/AR15 magazines with the strippers. Works with Mini-14 and other.223/5.56 magazines too.
The bandoleers have a strap so you can carry them over a shoulder and there is a safety pin on each strap so you can adjust them to suit your carry needs or to repair your clothing.
Not only that, the bandoleers can be modified by pulling the loose end of the white thread, which opens up the pocket a couple inches deeper, allowing you to store a loaded magazine in each pocket (after you load them up!).
This arrangement is really pretty cool and versatile, and the empty bandoleers can be used to tote around lots of other gear too, or you can shoot up the ammo and sell the bandos to someone else who wants to repack their own....just a repack kit goes for 5-10 bucks and these are in perfect shape!

The ammo packed in these is LC with the green tip, and Lake City is the best you can buy IMO.
62 grain steel core projectiles loaded up in boxer primed reloadable brass that is also an industry standard for high quality.

5.56 Ammo doesn't get any better than this!

$60.00 cash for each bandoleer (120 rounds)....I only have a couple cans packed like this.....if you buy all seven bandos in the can I'll toss in the can for free so you will have the whole GI package....$420 cash for the whole can of 840 rounds)

Prices are firm (I don't need to sell this) and NO SHIPPING (Don't ask!!)
Cash purchase face to face is how it works, no criminals, felons or terrorists.
I will ask you for a drivers license only to make sure you are 18 years old and not an illegal alien but I keep no records myself. I don't sell ammo for a living, just have a couple excess cans of really, REALLY good ammo that I probably will never get around to shooting up and can use the cash this summer for travel.

Thanks for looking!
